<h1>Download materials for larsoftobj @LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@ and dependencies</h1>

<h2>Release notes.</h2>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/cet-is/wiki/Supported_platforms">Supported Platforms</a></li>
  <li>To check available distributions, use <a href="http://scisoft.fnal.gov/scisoft/bundles/tools/getManifestList">getManifestList</a>: <br>
       getManifestList [bundle name] [bundle version]</li>
</ul>
  
<h2 id="scripts-binary">Download scripts for binary distributions.</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a type="application/x-sh" download href="http://scisoft.fnal.gov/scisoft/bundles/tools/pullProducts">pullProducts</a>
  <ul>
    <li>Will pull all products listed in the bundle manifest.</li>
    <li>This script will first check to see if a package is installed and will download the product only if not installed.</li>
    <li>Supported bundle <a href="http://scisoft.fnal.gov/scisoft/bundles/">list</a></li>
-    <li>USAGE: 
    <ul>
      <li>Download the script.</li>
      <li>chmod +x pullProducts</li>
      <li>Scientific Linux 6.x: <pre>./pullProducts &lt;product-directory&gt; slf6 larsoftobj-@LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@ &lt;prof|debug&gt;</pre></li>
      <li>Scientific Linux 7.x: <pre>./pullProducts &lt;product-directory&gt; slf7 larsoftobj-@LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@ &lt;prof|debug&gt;</pre></li>
      <li>Ubuntu 14: <pre>./pullProducts &lt;product-directory&gt; u14 larsoftobj-@LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@ &lt;prof|debug&gt;</pre></li>
      <li>Yosemite: <pre>./pullProducts &lt;product-directory&gt; d14 larsoftobj-@LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@ &lt;prof|debug&gt;</pre></li>
      <li>El Capitan (SIP disabled): <pre>./pullProducts &lt;product-directory&gt; d15 larsoftobj-@LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@ &lt;prof|debug&gt;</pre></li>
    </ul></li>
  </ul></li>
  <li>See <a href="https://cdcvs.fnal.gov/redmine/projects/cet-is-public/wiki/AboutQualifiers">About Qualifiers</a> for qualifier descriptions.</li>
  <li>We recommend downloading the prebuilt binaries whenever possible.</li>
</ul>


<h2 id="tarballs-contents">Packages</h2>
The following products are part of the larsoftobj suite:
<pre>   cetpkgsupport   @CETPKGSUPPORT_VERSION@
   cetbuildtools   @CETBUILDTOOLS_VERSION_LIST@
   cetlib          @CETLIB_VERSION@  @cet_qualifier@
   fhiclcpp        @FHICLCPP_VERSION@  @cet_qualifier@
   messagefacility @MESSAGEFACILITY_VERSION@  @cet_qualifier@
   canvas          @CANVAS_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@:nu
   gallery         @GALLERY_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@:nu
   nusimdata       @NUSIMDATA_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@
   larcoreobj      @LARCOREOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@
   lardataobj      @LARDATAOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@
   larsoftobj      @LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@ @cet_qualifier@</pre>

The following products are part of the basic larsoftobj bundle
<pre>     ups             @UPS_VERSION@
     upd             @UPD_VERSION@
     cmake           @OLD_CMAKE_VERSION@
     cmake           @CMAKE_VERSION@
     gcc             @GCC_VERSION@
     boost           @BOOST_VERSION@		@cet_qualifier@
     clhep           @CLHEP_VERSION@		@cet_qualifier@
     cppunit         @CPPUNIT_VERSION@		@cet_qualifier@
     fftw            @FFTW_VERSION@		@externals_qualifier@
     libxml2         @LIBXML2_VERSION@		@externals_qualifier@
     python          @PYTHON_VERSION@
     sqlite          @SQLITE_VERSION@
     tbb             @TBB_VERSION@		@cet_qualifier@
     root            @ROOT_VERSION@		@cet_qualifier@</pre>


<h2 id="scripts-source">Building from Source</h2>
  
NOTE: We recommend building from source only if you cannot use the prebuilt binaries.

<ul>
  <li><a type="application/x-sh" download href="http://scisoft.fnal.gov/scisoft/bundles/tools/checkPrerequisites">checkPrerequisites</a>
  <ul>
    <li>Will examine the system for the presence of known OS-level
    prerequisites (on RedHat derivatives, these will be RPMs) and list
    any deficiencies with remediation instructions. The script does not
    require admin privilege to run, but it is likely that any
    remediation will.</li>
    <li>USAGE:
    <ul>
      <li>Download the script.</li>
      <li><pre>chmod +x checkPrerequisites
./checkPrerequisites</li>
    </ul></li>
  </ul></li>
  <li><a type="application/x-sh" download href="http://scisoft.fnal.gov/scisoft/bundles/tools/pullProducts">pullProducts</a>
  <ul>
    <li>Will pull and expand source code tarballs preparatory to a build.</li>
    <li>This is the same script used to pull the binary distributions.</li>
    <li>USAGE:
    <ul>
      <li>Download the script.</li>
      <li><pre>chmod +x pullProducts
./pullProducts &lt;product-directory&gt; source  &lt;bundle&gt;</pre></li>
    </ul></li>
  </ul></li>
  <li label="buildFW"><a type="application/x-sh" download
  href="http://scisoft.fnal.gov/scisoft/bundles/tools/buildFW">buildFW</a>
  <ul>
    <li>Build all packages from source (as downloaded using the script
    above). Will obtain other source (cetlib, larsoftobj, etc.)
    direct from the FNAL Redmine repository as required.</li>
    <li>pullProducts downloads buildFW for you</.li>
    <li>USAGE:
      <pre>
Usage: buildFW [-h]
       buildFW &lt;options&gt; &lt;product_topdir&gt; &lt;build-spec&gt; &lt;bundle-spec&gt;

Options:

  -b    Specify basequal (REQUIRED: no default).
  -f    Force already-built packages to be rebuilt.
  -h    This help.
  -s    Specify version set for those packages requiring it
  -t    Make package tarfiles.
  -U    Force packaged version of UPS to be built and/or made current.

Arguments:

  product_topdir   Top directory for relocatable-UPS products area.

  build-spec    debug, opt or prof.

  bundle-spec   Bundle name and version, e.g., larsoftobj-@LARSOFTOBJ_VERSION@
    </pre></li>
  </ul></li>
</ul>

